The paper proposes a learning algorithm for navigating in a controlled Markov process (CMP) with non-stationary transition probabilities. This involves exploring the environment to gain knowledge and adapt to changes. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), and multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
